The paper proposes a method for accurate face contour extraction, which is a common task in computer vision and graphics. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The method involves sampling squares and extracting seams, which are common techniques in computer graphics and geometry processing, suggesting that cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.MM (Multimedia) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions experiments on face benchmark datasets, indicating that cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a possible sub-category. Finally, the proposed method involves integrating seams to form a continuous curve, which involves some level of machine learning and optimization, suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible sub-category as well.
